        "# STEP 1: Install required libraries (only if needed)\n",
        "!pip install textblob wordcloud openpyxl\n",
        "\n",
        "# STEP 2: Import libraries\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "from textblob import TextBlob\n",
        "from wordcloud import WordCloud\n",
        "\n",
        "# STEP 3: Upload the Excel file\n",
        "from google.colab import files\n",
        "uploaded = files.upload()  # Upload your college_event_feedback_2.xlsx\n",
        "\n",
        "# STEP 4: Read the Excel file\n",
        "df = pd.read_excel('college_event_feedback_2.xlsx')  # Make sure the filename matches\n",
        "df.head()\n",
        "\n",
        "# STEP 5: Clean the 'Rating' column\n",
        "# Remove non-numeric ratings\n",
        "df = df[pd.to_numeric(df['Rating'], errors='coerce').notnull()]\n",
        "df['Rating'] = df['Rating'].astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Drop rows with missing values (optional)\n",
        "df.dropna(inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# STEP 6: Bar chart of Ratings\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
        "sns.countplot(x='Rating', data=df)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Event Ratings Distribution\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Rating (1 = Poor, 5 = Excellent)\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Number of Students\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# STEP 7: Sentiment analysis on Comments\n",
        "df['Polarity'] = df['Comments'].apply(lambda x: TextBlob(str(x)).sentiment.polarity)\n",
        "df['Sentiment'] = df['Polarity'].apply(lambda x: 'Positive' if x > 0 else 'Negative' if x < 0 else 'Neutral')\n",
        "\n",
        "# STEP 8: Pie chart of sentiment\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))\n",
        "df['Sentiment'].value_counts().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%1.0f%%', startangle=90)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Feedback Sentiment Distribution\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# STEP 9: Word cloud of all comments\n",
        "text = \" \".join(df['Comments'].astype(str))\n",
        "wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color='white').generate(text)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n",
        "plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')\n",
        "plt.axis('off')\n",
        "plt.title(\"Word Cloud of Comments\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# STEP 10: Show summary stats\n",
        "print(\"Average Rating per Event:\")\n",
        "print(df.groupby(\"Event Name\")[\"Rating\"].mean().sort_values(ascending=False))\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nSentiment Counts:\")\n",
        "print(df['Sentiment'].value_counts())\n"
      ],
